reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Portable, fast charging, and good build quality.
reviews.reviewText: Parents are traveling soon so I got this as a gift for them. Charges fast, and uses USB-C so you don't have to deal with Apple's lightning cable in case you ever lose your charging cord. Solid build with a rubber coat, so it's durable, folds up nicely and comes with a nice carrying case. Even has some nice quality-of-life features such as the watch mount flipping up so the display faces you. Hoping this fixes some of the confusion every time I need to visit and can't charge my Android because of all the chargers being Lightning.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Road Warrior Approved - Worth every penny!
reviews.reviewText: I am a road warrior for both work and personal travel. I recently added Airpod Pros and an Apple Watch SE 2nd gen to my Apple collection which includes an iPhone 13Mini. This charges fits my needs to a "T".Build quality is very good. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Almost there, but with a caveat
reviews.reviewText: I couldn’t give it five stars but there’s a caveat. It might not be the device, it might be my device. Maybe. Unsure.I am still using and iPhone X (at least until I get my hands on the iPhone 15) with a thin, clear plastic case. Generally I have no issues with magnetic chargers with my iPhone X. This particular charger seems to charge slowly and make my iPhone X get warm. Is it the quality of the charger or is it that my iPhone X is actually too old and not officially supported? Maybe. The jury’s out until I get my iPhone 15. It charges my Apple Watch 7 just fine and it charges my AirPods Pro (1st generation) just fine. For all three items I have noticed that one must be careful to place the items exactly correctly, otherwise the charge will discontinue before finishing the job. But it works. The Apple Watch obviously needs to get a good magnetic connection to the charging disc otherwise it will not charge. For the AirPods Pro and the iPhone it should not be required to place with millimeter precision, just “centered”.I find it hard to judge this one. Maybe it’s not great but great for the price. Would I buy it again? No, but only because I would want to try another brand if for no other reason than to compare and contrast.
